    "last_edit_date" : 1441596716,
    "creation_date" : 1416149938,
    "answer_id" : 26958314,
    "question_id" : 3930210,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Another option is the static <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#valueOf-int-\"><code>String.valueOf</code></a> method.</p>\n\n<pre><code>String.valueOf(i)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>It <em>feels</em> slightly more right than <code>Integer.toString(i)</code> to me. When the type of i changes, for example from <code>int</code> to <code>double</code>, the code will stay correct.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6630179,
      "reputation" : 145,
      "user_id" : 5119121,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-idGV_ByTa3U/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/mdu0_Odm3oI/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Shailej Shimpi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5119121/shailej-shimpi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1439551548,
    "creation_date" : 1439551548,
    "answer_id" : 32008929,
    "question_id" : 3930210,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here \n<code>Integer.toString</code> calls the static method in the class Integer. It does not require the object to call.</p>\n\n<p>If you call <code>new Integer(i)</code> you first create an instance of type Integer, which is a full Java object encapsulating the value of your int i. Then you call the <code>toString</code> method on it to ask it to return a string representation of itself.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7256854,
      "reputation" : 151,
      "user_id" : 5535196,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-4Qa1mAJ06K0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABQ/0ViteV1q2jU/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Nathan Waite",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5535196/nathan-waite"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 15,
    "last_activity_date" : 1509883865,
    "last_edit_date" : 1509883865,
    "creation_date" : 1446845996,
    "answer_id" : 33576133,
    "question_id" : 3930210,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Although I like fhucho's recommendation of </p>\n\n<pre><code>String.valueOf(i)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The irony is that this method actually calls </p>\n\n<pre><code>Integer.toString(i)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Thus, use <code>String.valueOf(i)</code> if you like how it reads and you don't need radix, but also knowing that it is less efficient than <code>Integer.toString(i)</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1820446,
      "reputation" : 4200,
      "user_id" : 1654631,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 0,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c8d805f46866346046b4527bee7d8a24?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Shiv Buyya",
